# Repository skills

The baseline contains portable repository-local package-structure, prd-writer,
prd-review, prd-implementer, and effect-client-wrapper skills. Repository docs
and commands own local truth. A separately installed global skill may provide
generic tooling, but local workflows never require its filesystem path.
Validate SKILL.md, references, and `agents/openai.yaml` whenever a skill changes.

The reserved docs-maintainer interface is the repository profile in
`.agents/skills/package-structure/references/repository-profile.md`: it names the
docs router, semantic owners, exact checks, README rules, generated/reference
owners, runbooks, proof, authority, archive, and mirror policy. HGI-style local
docs-maintainer skills route to that profile instead of copying repository truth.
